title: Lauren Condie Resume
text:
Contact Information
Phone: 469-318-6171
Email: laurencondie4@gmail.com
LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/lauren-condie


Skills Summary

Statistical Analysis: RStudio, Python, SQL Workbench, Qualtrics

Microsoft Office Tools: Excel, Word, PowerPoint, Outlook

Soft Skills: Detail-oriented, highly organized, strong analytical and critical thinking skills



Education
Bachelor of Data Science | Brigham Young University - Idaho | Rexburg, Idaho
August 2023 – Present
- GPA: 3.95
- Minor in Data Science
- Brigham Young University Scholarship Recipient
High School Diploma | Homeschool Co-Op | Forney, Texas
August 2019 – May 2023
- GPA: 4.0
- Classical education
- Completed dual-credit coursework through Dallas and Lone Star College


Experience
Research Specialist - Team Lead | Brigham Young University - Idaho | Rexburg, Idaho
March 2024 – September 2025
- Recruited participants, conducted, and analyzed results for 30+ focus groups
- Designed and administered surveys for university-wide initiatives using Qualtrics
- Conducted in-depth interviews with students and faculty to collect data and insights
- Utilized Excel and PowerPoint to interpret and visualize findings
- Trained new hires on research methods, data analysis, and software tools
Restaurant Team Member | Panera Bread | Forney, Texas
December 2022 – December 2023
- Provided accurate, efficient service ensuring quality and customer satisfaction
- Trained new team members through modeling and coaching
- Adapted to changing tasks in a fast-paced environment
- Demonstrated reliability with flexible scheduling
Business Owner/Operator | Condie Cooking School | Forney, Texas
May 2023 – August 2023
- Founded and ran multiple 5-week cooking courses for students (ages 6–17)
- Managed curriculum, recipe planning, ingredient purchasing, and safety protocols


Volunteer Work
Volunteer Library Page | Rockwall County Library | Rockwall, Texas
May 2018 – May 2022
- Organized and restocked library materials with accuracy and attention to detail
- Catalogued and sorted over 100 items per session, learning library systems thoroughly
